The paper discusses the problem of automatic program learning, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The two competing approaches mentioned, neural program synthesis and neural program induction, are both subfields of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses rule-based program synthesis, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The modified attention RNN used in the neural models is a technique commonly used in natural language processing and sequence modeling, which are subfields of programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of the neural models to noise in real-world data, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY).
